This will be the first of my informational series videos coming in HOT 🔥 - today we’re talking about self-sabotage and how to get out of the vicious negative thought loop cycle. I understand this frustrating cycle all too well and want to share some tools that help me recognize and end it for good. ⁣
⁣
Tell me your thoughts and what other topics you’d love to see in these series! I already have a bunch brewing and ready to be released 😉⁣
⁣
Hola, mis amigos ferales 👊🏼 Este será el primero de mis videos de serie informativa🔥. Hoy estamos hablando sobre el autosabotaje y cómo salir del círculo vicioso del pensamiento negativo. Entiendo muy bien este ciclo frustrante y quiero compartir algunas herramientas que me ayudan a mi a reconocerlo y terminarlo para de una vez por todas.⁣
⁣
¡Porfa díganme lo que piensan sobre el video y qué otros temas les encantaría ver en esta serie! Ya tengo un montón en preparación y listos para ser lanzados 😉

Ireleasing in less than 44 hours! (Friday 12/11/20 @ 10AM EST!) before this pre-sale launches I wanted to share some thoughts around my style of coaching. 

Any other questions save them and ask me this Sunday, where I open a Q&A from A-Z on this particular program, what to expect, what it focuses on, what you’ll need, and more!

Mi próximo programa, Divine You💫, se lanzará en menos de 44 horas! ( este viernes 12/11/20 @ 10AM EST!) Antes del lanzamiento de esta preventa, quería compartir algunas ideas sobre mi estilo de coaching. (Abajo la traducción!)

Cualquier otra pregunta, guárdelas y pregúnteme este domingo, donde abro una sesión de preguntas y respuestas de la A a la Z sobre este programa en particular, qué esperar, en qué se enfoca, qué necesitará y más.

[He notado un patrón en respeto con los clientes y coaches, y quería compartir algunas ideas al respecto; mi estilo de coaching no se basa necesariamente en problemas. Por supuesto que estoy aquí para ayudarte si tenes alguna cosa en particular en la que quieras trabajar. Pero también trabajo con mis clientes en sus pasiones, desarrollándolos ayudándolos a evolucionar, comprender y expandir la visión de sí mismos, sus roles emocionales. Muchos de mis clientes si tienen problemas y quieren resolverlos y tomar acciones y activar ciertas habilidades y fortalezas, sin duda, el punto es que los problemas no están excluidos del coaching y no son necesarios.

A medida que te ayude con una visión mas amplia de tu personalidad, la consecuencia natural es que muchos problemas, comportamientos y dudas, desaparecen. Pero cuando te estás enfocando constantemente en "no soy suficiente" o "cómo puedo superar mi ansiedad por esto", ahí es donde queda tu enfoque, en la ansiedad por no ser suficiente.

Por lo tanto, no ignoramos los problemas y las ansiedades, sino que también trabajamos a partir de un entendimiento en el que realmente caes en tu yo auténtico, tu propósito, tu fuerza. Y a medida que empieces a comprender cuándo te salís de eso en un patrón o un sistema de creencias que no es tuyo, te darás cuenta ma rápido y el resultado es que los problemas . (Continúa en comentarios 👇🏽)

node.text:
Today was an incredibly huge day for me. As I’ve shared with you all , these past few weeks have been full of a lot of interpersonal development and growth. Within myself and within my team. 

But today along with the motivation and encouragement from my husband @luisenriquepzia 
I’ve committed to competing in one of the hardest races in the world, the @ironmantri 

I’m feeling so many emotions right now, from anxiety, to fear, and even self doubt. But I’m also feeling excited, and motivated , in ways that I haven’t felt in such a long time, (probably why I said like 1000 times in this video😅). This is one of the greatest challenges I’m yet to undertake, and it’s part of the journey to becoming the whole and balanced human that I’m meant to be.

When  was the last time that you took on a challenge that was outside of your comfort zone? Let me know in the comments!

Y realizar movimientos así en la arena ya es de por si super desafiante si no estas acostumbrad@ por eso quiero que no seas tan dur@ con vos mism@, date un break y perdonate por no ser tan perfect@ en todo, date tiempo para progresar, lo que ves en mi y en otras personas que son “mejores” que vos es solo TIEMPO, PRACTICA, y CONSTANCIA. Y sabes que yo estoy aquí siempre, para darte la mano en tu camino, para guiarte y aprender, y realizar tus metas. De hecho estoy por lanzar mi siguiente reto, inscribite ya! Help you to go through your days, organize ideas, and just bring calm to any situation that you may experience on your regular days. The mind is like water when is turbulent is difficult to see when is calm everything become more clear, most of the times we see the problems bigger than what they really are. And remember that you can meditate EVERYWHERE and ANY TIME!⁣
⁣
Chic@s la próxima vez haré una meditación en español. Ya que no sería inteligente poner subtítulos porque el punto de meditaciones es dar tu 100% atención. Los quiero! ❤️ y hasta la próxima!

Knowledge is power. And with that power you can be your ultimate you. ⁣

I have been dealing with some gut health problems, which made me wonder what else could be going wrong internally. And while listening to a podcast @insidetracker was mentioned as a tool to analyze data from our blood and DNA to help better understand our body & help reach optimal health goals. ⁣
⁣
I’ve done full panels before but I was never able to truly understand how to improve the biomarkers that were off, that data can be super overwhelming and doctors aren’t very helpful in dissecting the information all they do is give you whatever you’re lacking without rhyme or reason. ⁣
⁣
And the right way to get your internal health to optimal levels, you need someone who is able to guide you in understanding the data to make the right supplementation and nutritional choices. ⁣
⁣
Now I have a protocol that makes sense to follow in order to get my energy, immune health and brain function to not just normalized levels but OPTIMAL, this translates in better physical performance and mental ability. About 70% of diseases stem from our gut I don’t have time to get sick, and I want this machine working like a Ferrari ⚡️⁣
⁣
I’m excited for my partnership with Inside Tracker to give away🤟🏼⁣
⚡️An ultimate blood test ($589 value)⁣

‼️To enter click the link in my bio!⁣

Información es poder. Y con ese poder, podés ser la mejor versión de vos mismx.⁣

⁣

How can you create a healthy, long-term, stick-with-it diet?⁣
⁣
A fad diets won’t help your weight loss. Managing your caloric intake, will. We make loosing weight much more complicated that it actually is. The principle is simple; consume more calories than you expend and you’ll put on weight, consume less calories than you expend and you’ll loose weight. ⁣
⁣
So why do we over-complicate it? We always try to find the easy way, the comfortable way, the way that doesn’t invoke changing our way of doing things. ⁣
⁣
In order to loose weight, or gain weight, there are no short cuts, or tricks…what you need to adopt is healthy sustainable progressive habits into your life. Stop letting your mind lead you to the yo-yo effect.⁣
⁣
This is why we launched simple education to our newest program, the feral project. ⁣
⁣
You won’t have to stop eating your favorite foods, instead you’ll have the right tools to get you to your goal, without making unrealistic lifestyle changes. I believe education is fundamental in progression, so the team and I created weekly workshops where you’ll learn:⁣

* How to Cultivate Healthy Habits & Bullet-proof Schedule ⁣
* Build a Healthy Relationship with Food⁣
* Addressing Anxiety & Trauma with Breath and Hipnosis Meditation⁣
* Cultivating Creativity, Being in the Present Moment & Motivation⁣

🥲Crying for me in some workouts isn’t uncommon, scientifically speaking when we're exhausted, our emotional brain is less inhibited, which implies it's easier for us to burst out in tears. This was my second to last set of the day.⁣
⁣
Why do I show this video?—No it doesn’t mean I’m ‘suffering’, because I’m not, I VERY much enjoy all that comes with MY training and being pushed to my limits within reason—What I’m showing, is that we can experience a range of emotions during exercise, not limited to crying, we may also be more aware of positive emotions like enthusiasm, joy, and euphoria. ⁣
⁣
And while we often try to dissociate from our bodies while we work out—we crank our music or absorb technology as we tune out physical discomfort—mindful exercise allows us to tune into our bodies.⁣
⁣
Why is this important? Our bodies can hold tension and negative emotions that can be released during physical activity.⁣
⁣
It’s another outlet to connect with ourselves and release anything that is trapped inside. So whatever feeling you experience in your next workout. I urge you not to hold it in, let it out, without judging, just acknowledge it and release it. ⁣
⁣
Thank you @ibrahim.nino for your cheers and encouragement to push harder on each set🤟🏼⁣
⁣
If you want to learn more about my training & coaching style, DM ME now⚡️❤️ Pushing YOU to be your best self means finding what YOU love and molding it to YOUR lifestyle💪🏼⁣
⁣
